    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="678"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hirsch</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 217.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am gratified to learn by your No. 284 of 7th
                    instant, that your note of 15th December last to the Porte, has apparently had
                    the effect to cause the unconditional issue to the Rev. Henry Easson of Latakia,
                    of the building permit which he had asked in vain of the local authorities.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
